gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 113, Pacers 111
gameRecap.excerpt: Minnesota defeats Indiana, 113-111. For Minnesota, Anthony Edwards led the way with 44 points, six rebounds, two steals, and two blocks while Rudy Gobert added 18 points, 14 rebounds, and three blocks in the victory. Pascal Siakam tallied 24 points and four rebounds with Tyrese Haliburton recording his league-leading 36th PTS/AST double-double with 23 points and 13 assists for Indiana in the losing effort. Minnesota improves to 44-19 on the season, while Indiana moves to 35-29 with the loss.
